    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-24T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-24T11:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890b.6363 Gulf Oil Corporation/26: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-24T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 24, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 24—1:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Department’s 50, February 2, 2 [<hi rend="italic">1</hi>] p.m. In informal
                    conversation yesterday with Foreign Office I took occasion to refer to
                    representations made by me as reported on top of <ref target="#pg_3">page
                        3</ref> of Embassy’s despatch 2482, December 29,<note n="5" xml:id="d5fn5">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_4">p. 4</ref>, paragraph
                        beginning, “On December 29 Mr. <persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            >Atherton</persName> saw <persName corresp="#p_OSL1">Sir Lancelot
                            Oliphant</persName>…”</note> and to point out that according to reports
                    reaching me Anglo-Persian Oil Company geologists had <pb facs="0097" n="7"
                        xml:id="pg_7"/> recently arrived in Koweit having brought drilling
                    machinery, et cetera, to carry on exploration work.</p>
                <p>Despatch by pouch.<note n="6" xml:id="d5fn6">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
